    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Louisville Ky</placeName>
                <date>8 Dec 5617/1857</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd I. Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Revd. &amp; Dr Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">I should have replied earlier to yours<lb/> of <date>4<hi rend="sup"
                        >th</hi></date> ulto. But have been confined to my bed since<lb/> the
                        <date>6<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> and only left it yesterday. I thank you
                for<lb/> yours and as soon as I can move about to raise<lb/> the funds for Books
                will do so. I note what you say concerning <persName>Mr Gotthelf's</persName>
                remarks as to what<lb/> I owe on your account. I understood from him that<lb/> he
                had settled up with you for my subscription<lb/> to the Occident some time ago and
                also for<lb/> the Bibles had: however if you will oblige<lb/> me with a statement of
                what you conceive<lb/> my indebtedness to be, I will thank you, as I<lb/> shall then
                have something tangible to lay<lb/> before him. On your reply I may explain<lb/>
                more fully. Please attend to it. Wishing you<lb/> many years of Long Life &amp;
                Health for the<lb/> benefit of our Holy Cause I remain</p>
            <p rend="indent(11)">Truly Yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(11)">
                <persName role="author">A J H Bernal</persName>
            </p>
            <p>P. S. There is a <persName>Revd. Dr. De Banco</persName><lb/> here candidate as Rab
                in the old <add>ליה</add> He claims to<lb/> be from <placeName>Hamburg</placeName>
                son of an Italian. Has been<lb/> in the <placeName>States</placeName> ten years, in
                    <placeName>N.Y.</placeName> and <placeName>N. O.</placeName> Did<lb/> you ever
                hear of him before? I did not.</p>
            <p>P.S. Altho' the Commit have not made a final report on the<lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">Destructive</hi> Prayer Book of <persName>Wise</persName>, yet
                by a<lb/> resolution of the School Directors, it has been<lb/> adopted in their
                School. Can nothing be done<lb/> to put a stop to such nefarious proceedings,
                thus<lb/> poisoning the minds of youth.</p>
        </body>
